where a late-winter storm left ice up to half an inch thick on streets and 
closed most public schools. Much of the eastern part of the nation, from Maine 
to Alabama, was digging out from a storm that moved in from the Midwest 
overnight. Temperatures in the Northeast dropped below zero in many areas. 
