<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
CITIZEN OF YEAR MOLESTED BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Galt civic leader and scoutmaster has admitted that he molested eight boys 
and punished some of them by making them stand naked, according to court 
documents. Allen Lee Trueman, 42, pleaded no contest to eight felony charges 
when he was arraigned in Sacramento Municipal Court. A carpenter, who was named 
Galt's Citizen of the Year in 1988 for his volunteer work, Trueman initially 
denied molesting the 8- to 14-year-old boys in his home. But court records said 
he later told investigators he had bathed some of the boys, tickled their 
genitals and made them stand naked when they misbehaved. "I do what I do 
because I'm searching for satisfaction," police quoted Trueman as saying. "When 
I'm helping the boys, I need to feel needed and loved in return." Trueman told 
police he is dropping out of all Scout activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
