<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Terrorist organizations seem certain to eventually acquire chemical, biological 
and even nuclear weapons, a conference in Stockholm was told. "It's not a 
question of 'if' but of 'when' it will happen. It's just a matter of time," 
said Yonah Alexander, director of the Institute for Studies in International 
Terrorism at the State University of New York. "We have to face the danger that 
a terrorist incident could provoke a nuclear confrontation, and both the United 
States and Soviet Union are aware of this," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
