<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUPREME COURT ON CHILD ABUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bravo! Rehnquist has finally said it! No hedging, no beating around the Bush. 
The Supreme Court rules that "Nothing in the language of the due process clause 
itself requires the state to protect the life, liberty and property of its 
citizens against invasion." Yes, ladies and gentlemen, it's loud and clear: The 
Administration is washing its hands. 
</P>
<P>
If a policeman walks by while you are clobbered on the street, and he doesn't 
move a finger to protect you, under the new ruling you can't sue him or anybody 
else. If the possibly exonerating evidence in your trial is "lost" by the 
officials (biased or not), you have only yourself to blame. Yes, you are on 
your own. 
</P>
<P>
Naturally, you still have to pay your taxes; the Constitution does not protect 
you from the IRS, but whether or not the services in return will be forthcoming 
is left to the benevolence of the state agencies. See if they feel like it. If, 
in the midst of a disintegrating welfare system, skyrocketing medical and 
insurance costs, inflation, bailouts, homelessness, drugs and cultural 
deprivation, you still had any doubts as to whose interest this Administration 
is representing, set them aside now. Just look up and count your thousand 
points of light! 
</P>
<P>
ENDRE HULES 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 
</P>
</TEXT>
