<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST BASKETBALL TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
IRVINE WOMEN WIN BIG WEST PLAYOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC Irvine women's basketball team, sparked by a 16-0 run late in the game, 
took a 60-49 victory over University of the Pacific in a Big West Conference 
playoff game Tuesday at Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (9-19) will play Cal State Long Beach today at 3:30 p.m. at the Long 
Beach Sports Arena. Pacific led, 44-41, with 7 minutes 39 seconds left when 
Irvine went on the 16-0 run. 
</P>
<P>
Kathy Lizarraga scored 20 points and was six of 12 from three-point range to 
lead Irvine. Jenny Lee had 11 points and Shurrell Johnson had 10 points for 
Irvine. Natasha Parks had a team-high 15 rebounds. 
</P>
