<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
7-RUN RALLY LIFTS RIO MESA OVER ALEMANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID SALKIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore Dmitri Young had three hits and five runs batted in and Rio Mesa High 
pushed across seven runs in the decisive sixth inning as the Spartans defeated 
Alemany, 13-8, in a Westside tournament game Tuesday at Rio Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 8-6, in the bottom of the sixth, the Spartans launched their assault 
when Young scored Carlos Cendejas from third with a single. 
</P>
<P>
A sacrifice fly by Steve Soliz tied the score, 8-8, and the Spartans took their 
first lead when Alemany's Jeff Daniels threw a wild pitch that allowed Young to 
score from third. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa (2-1) got to Daniels for one more run, then touched up reliever Matt 
Delavinge for three more when Cendejas, batting for the second time in the 
inning, ripped a bases-loaded double down the left-field line. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany (2-1) led, 6-0, entering the bottom of the first, but Young, the state 
freshman player of the year last season, belted a two-run home run. Young 
employed his power again in the fourth, drawing Rio Mesa to within 8-6 with a 
two-run homer to left-center field. DAVID SALKIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
