<P>
A living room set that was owned by composer Ludwig Von Beethoven until his 
death in 1827 and was part of his estate brought about $8,333 at an auction 
Tuesday in Paris. The five-piece ensemble was purchased by an unidentified 
American. The set consisted of a love seat with a curved back and arms in solid 
walnut, three fan-backed chairs covered in green felt and a small laminated 
table. ALEENE MacMINN 
