SAN DIEGO SPOTLIGHT: SAN DIEGO ENTERTAINMENT BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If you've got a strong arts background and the ability to withstand heat that 
would glaze a clay vase, San Diego has an opening today for a new public arts 
administrator. Joyce Selber, who's held the job since its creation in October, 
1986, announced her resignation Tuesday to assume the post of exectuive 
director of the Commission for the Arts in Pasadena. The San Diego public arts 
administrator's job, one that rests in the cross fire between the arts 
community and city government, pays $45,698 a year. Apply to the San Diego 
Commission for Arts and Culture. 
