<TEXT>
<P>
GM Offers New Rebates: In an effort to boost its softening sales, General 
Motors began four new incentive programs, offering 4.9% short-term car loans on 
some top-selling models, such as the Corsica and Beretta. Analysts said the 
rebate programs would likely help improve March sales, which have lagged behind 
the strong pace of 1988. Ford and Chrysler also are offering 4.9% financing 
rates, but their programs are not as extensive. GM's inventory of unsold cars 
at the end of February was estimated at 85 days, while Ford's was 81 days and 
Chrysler's 94 days. The industry considers a 65- to 70-day supply of cars 
acceptable. 
</P>
