<P>
Pacific Enterprises OKs Holder Plan: The board of Pacific Enterprises, the Los 
Angeles-based parent of Southern California Gas Co. and Thrifty Corp., has 
adopted a shareholders' rights plan. The plan is intended to protect 
shareholders in the event of an unsolicited attempt to acquire Pacific 
Enterprises. "The plan was not adopted in response to any effort to acquire 
control of Pacific Enterprises and the board of directors is unaware of any 
such effort," Chairman Paul A. Miller said. "The plan is not intended to 
prevent a takeover of Pacific Enterprises and will not do so. However, it 
should discourage any attempt to acquire Pacific Enterprises in a manner or on 
terms not approved by the board of directors as being in the best interest of 
shareholders." 
</P>
