<HEADLINE>
<P>
VARIAN SAYS IT WON'T FIGHT FTC DECISION ON DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PALO ALTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Varian Associates said it will not fight the Federal Trade Commission's 
decision to block the $65.8-million sale of its vacuum products division to the 
BOC Group of Britain. 
</P>
<P>
The company said it had been notified by the FTC that the agency would not 
approve the planned sale and had authorized its staff to seek a preliminary 
court injunction against the deal. 
</P>
<P>
The FTC said the combination of the Varian division with BOC's Edwards High 
Vacuum business would control too large a share of the market for a specific 
leak-detection device. 
</P>
<P>
Varian Associates produces systems and components for communications, defense, 
scientific, medical and industrial markets. 
</P>
