<TEXT>
<P>
The General Accounting Office told Congress, in a report released today, that 
states have found problems ranging from physical and sexual abuse to improperly 
stored food and trash at rest homes and similar residential facilities for the 
elderly and mentally ill. 
</P>
<P>
It reported on the board-and-care homes, which are residences of last resort 
for many aged and mentally ill people. "It is frightening how little we know 
about board-and-care homes," said Sen. John Heinz (R-Pa.), ranking Republican 
on the Senate Special Committee on Aging. "This is an industry out of sight and 
out of control." 
