<P>
PEPSI PULLS MADONNA AD ON MTV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepsi-Cola Co. canceled plans to run a two-minute commercial with pop star 
Madonna on MTV after the cable network started airing the singer's 
controversial new music video, a source close to Pepsi said today. 
</P>
<P>
The Pepsi ad with Madonna, which is dubbed "Make a Wish" and includes an 
abbreviated version of her new song, "Like a Prayer," debuted last Thursday on 
television shows in 40 countries. 
</P>
<P>
The next day, MTV began running a separate music video that heralded the launch 
of the singer's new song. The video shows Madonna in a black slip, dancing 
among burning crosses and seeking refuge in a church where she kisses a statue 
of a saint who comes to life. 
</P>
<P>
Pepsi had planned to run the two-minute ad last weekend on MTV, but withheld it 
while the video is running, the source said. 
