<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Mears, a three-time Indianapolis 500 winner, and a companion were fined 
$20,000 each and forfeited the skins of two grizzly bears after pleading no 
contest to misdemeanor game violations in Alaska. 
</P>
<P>
Businessman Michael Stier said that he and Mears, both of Bakersfield, were 
unaware they were violating state law because they were hunting with a licensed 
guide during a 1987 trip. But Stier conceded that "ignorance is no excuse." 
Mears was unavailable for comment. 
</P>
